	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I was bored and decided to do a little research on this fellow using my Lvl 9 Bard. Here's what I found:<BR>
<BR>
The Boards are correct. You cannot hit him with a standard weapon ie: tarnished sword, ect. You must use a magical weapon or spell. <BR>
<BR>
He casts for approx 6pts damage and can cast from quite a distance...if you can see him..he can cast against you.<BR>
<BR>
Word of caution to other fledgling Bards. Make sure your Songs are already cast because when he hits you, it cancels your song...and he hits quite rapidly. I never got my melee song up and running (don't try this like I did when you have a lag problem like I did).<BR>
<BR>
If you have to run..do NOT run to the guards for help..they won't. I ran past the guards and well beyond the gates..he cast 6pts damage on me and even though he was standing next to the guards, they didn't touch him. Needless to say..I ran to W Freeport Zone..and yes, he followed. Just a side note..this is the only time I've seen him run ;)<BR>
<BR>
It's best to run for the North Ro zone it's alot closer anyway.<BR>
I plan on going back when I have a solid link and pay him a visit.<BR>
~killing him softly with her songs~  ;)<BR>
Happy hunting everyone!<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

